  "prompt": "Is power steering fluid the same as brake fluid?",
  "response": "No, power steering fluid and brake fluid are not the same. They are different types of hydraulic fluids with distinct compositions and purposes:\n\n1. Power steering fluid:\n- Used in power steering systems to help reduce steering effort\n- Typically has a lighter viscosity\n- Often red or pink in color\n- Specific to power steering systems\n\n2. Brake fluid:\n- Used in hydraulic brake systems to transfer force and create braking pressure\n- Usually clear or slightly yellow\n- Higher boiling point and different chemical composition\n- Specifically designed for brake system requirements\n\nThese fluids are not interchangeable, and using the wrong fluid can damage your vehicle's systems.",
